🧠 How It Works
1. Scrape Data
Run the Python script to fetch and save the latest data:

bash
Copy
Edit
python main.py
This will create:

products_data.csv

ecommerce_data.json

2. View in Browser
Open index.html directly in your browser (no server needed):

bash
Copy
Edit
# Just double-click or use:
open index.html
Make sure ecommerce_data.json is in the same directory.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Layer	Tools Used
Scraper	Python, requests, csv, json
Frontend	HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
Data Source	FakeStoreAPI

📂 Output Files
File Name	Description
products_data.csv	Structured product table (for analysis)
ecommerce_data.json	Full export including categories, ratings, and timestamp

